-- Egypt, Libya and Tunisia Consider Visa-Free Zone to Boost Trade
-- B y   S a l m a   E l   W a r d a n y
-- 2012-07-30T13:17:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-30/egypt-libya-and-tunisia-consider-visa-free-zone-to-boost-trade.html
Egypt , Tunisia and Libya are
considering changes to allow for visa-free travel in a bid to
bolster trade and economic cooperation, the state-run Middle
East News Agency reported, citing Egyptian Foreign Minister
Mohamed Kamel Amr.  The three countries agreed to put into effect a so-called
Cairo Declaration that was announced yesterday, the agency said.
The declaration aims to facilitate commerce, encourage
investment, and fight terrorism, drug smuggling and illegal
migration.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Salma El Wardany in Cairo at 
